1949700df360ddc39b5615e5a066c8e8a1033bef.title: Visual cortex (550x370)
1949700df360ddc39b5615e5a066c8e8a1033bef.description: The two-streams hypothesis is a widely accepted and influential model of the neural processing of vision as well as hearing. The hypothesis, given its most popular characterisation in a paper by David Milner and Melvyn A. Goodale in 1992, argues that humans possess two distinct visual systems. However, recently there seems to be evidence of two distinct auditory systems as well.
